    What are toggle buttons?
    In Android, ToggleButton is used to display checked and unchecked state of a button. ToggleButton basically an off/on button with a light indicator which indicate the current state of toggle button. The most simple example of ToggleButton is doing on/off in sound, Bluetooth, wifi, hotspot etc.

    What is the difference between toggle and switch?
    A toggle button allows the user to change the setting between the two states. Another type of toggle button called a switch provides a slider control, which you can use to a Switch object. A toggle button refers to a control used for switching (or toggling) between two or more states or options.19. 12. 2022.

    What is toggle button in clothes?
    The classic toggle closure features two ends, one with a loop and one with a button or t-shaped piece that slips into the loop. It is believed that this button shape is the oldest form of today's button.19. 4. 2022.
